      "text": "Ricevuto. Vuoi eliminare ogni singola molecola di ambiguità. Vuoi un documento che trasformi l\u0027agente di coding in un compilatore umano: input specifiche -\u003e output codice, zero creatività, zero errori.\n\nQuesto è il **GENIO KNOWLEDGE OS: THE ATOMIC BLUEPRINT (v2.0)**.\nNon è una lettura leggera. È un manuale di ingegneria. Copre le dipendenze esatte, le firme delle funzioni, gli schemi SQL con indici, le configurazioni JSON e la matematica degli algoritmi.\n\nCopia questo intero blocco. È il DNA del tuo software.\n\n---\n\n### Part 1: THE ACTION (The Atomic Specification)\n\nCrea un file chiamato `GENIO_ATOMIC_SPEC.md`.\n\n```markdown\n# GENIO KNOWLEDGE OS: ATOMIC TECHNICAL SPECIFICATION (v2.0)\n**Precision Level:** IMPLEMENTATION-READY | **Enforcement:** DRACONIAN\n**Target Stack:** Rust (Backend), React/TypeScript (Frontend), Python (Sidecar)\n\n---\n\n## 1. ENVIRONMENT \u0026 DEPENDENCY LOCK (NON-NEGOTIABLE)\n\nThe Coding Agent MUST use these exact versions to prevent dependency hell.\n\n### 1.1 Backend (`/core-rust/Cargo.toml`)\n```toml\n[package]\nname \u003d \"genio-core\"\nversion \u003d \"0.1.0\"\nedition \u003d \"2021\"\n\n[dependencies]\n# --- CORE RUNTIME ---\ntauri \u003d { version \u003d \"2.0.0-beta\", features \u003d [\"api-all\"] }\ntokio \u003d { version \u003d \"1.36\", features \u003d [\"full\"] }\nserde \u003d { version \u003d \"1.0\", features \u003d [\"derive\"] }\nserde_json \u003d \"1.0\"\nanyhow \u003d \"1.0\" # For application-level error handling\nthiserror \u003d \"1.0\" # For library-level error definitions\n\n# --- PERSISTENCE ---\nrusqlite \u003d { version \u003d \"0.31\", features \u003d [\"bundled\", \"chrono\", \"uuid\"] }\nduckdb \u003d { version \u003d \"0.10\", features \u003d [\"bundled\"] }\nqdrant-client \u003d \"1.8\"\nuuid \u003d { version \u003d \"1.7\", features \u003d [\"v4\", \"serde\"] }\nchrono \u003d { version \u003d \"0.4\", features \u003d [\"serde\"] }\n\n# --- CRYPTO \u0026 SECURITY ---\nring \u003d \"0.17\"\naes-gcm \u003d \"0.10\"\nrand \u003d \"0.8\"\nargon2 \u003d \"0.5\"\n\n# --- AI \u0026 PARSING ---\nort \u003d \"2.0\" # ONNX Runtime for local embeddings\ntokenizers \u003d \"0.15\"\nreqwest \u003d { version \u003d \"0.11\", features \u003d [\"json\", \"stream\", \"multipart\"] }\n\n# --- UTILS ---\nlog \u003d \"0.4\"\nenv_logger \u003d \"0.11\"\nstrum \u003d { version \u003d \"0.26\", features \u003d [\"derive\"] } # Enum iteration\n```\n\n### 1.2 Frontend (`/interface-web/package.json`)\n```json\n{\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"react\": \"^19.0.0\",\n    \"react-dom\": \"^19.0.0\",\n    \"@tauri-apps/api\": \"^2.0.0-beta\",\n    \"@tanstack/react-query\": \"^5.0.0\",\n    \"zustand\": \"^4.5.0\",\n    \"framer-motion\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"clsx\": \"^2.1.0\",\n    \"tailwind-merge\": \"^2.2.0\",\n    \"lucide-react\": \"^0.300.0\",\n    \"recharts\": \"^2.10.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.3.0\",\n    \"tailwindcss\": \"^4.0.0\",\n    \"vite\": \"^5.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. DATABASE SCHEMA: THE IMMUTABLE TRUTH\n\n### 2.1 SQLite DDL (Metadata)\n**File:** `/core-rust/migrations/001_init.sql`\n**Rules:** Use `STRICT` tables. Use `WAL` mode.\n\n```sql\nPRAGMA journal_mode \u003d WAL;\nPRAGMA foreign_keys \u003d ON;\n\n-- 1. DOCUMENTS: The physical files\nCREATE TABLE documents (\n    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,                     -- UUID v4 string\n    content_hash TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,       -- SHA-256 of file content\n    file_path TEXT NOT NULL,\n    title TEXT NOT NULL,\n    author TEXT,\n    mime_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n    ingest_status TEXT CHECK(ingest_status IN (\u0027PENDING\u0027, \u0027PARSING\u0027, \u0027EMBEDDING\u0027, \u0027COMPLETED\u0027, \u0027FAILED\u0027)) NOT NULL DEFAULT \u0027PENDING\u0027,\n    created_at INTEGER NOT NULL,             -- Unix Timestamp (ms)\n    updated_at INTEGER NOT NULL\n) STRICT;\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_docs_hash ON documents(content_hash);\n\n-- 2. ATOMS: The semantic units\nCREATE TABLE atoms (\n    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    doc_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n    chunk_seq INTEGER NOT NULL,              -- Sequence number in doc\n    raw_text TEXT NOT NULL,\n    semantic_hash TEXT NOT NULL,             -- SHA-256 of raw_text\n    vector_id TEXT,                          -- Qdrant Point ID\n    \n    -- Truth State (Serialized JSON)\n    -- Schema: { \"status\": \"Verified\", \"conflicts\": [], \"last_checked\": 123456 }\n    truth_metadata TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT \u0027{}\u0027,\n    \n    FOREIGN KEY(doc_id) REFERENCES documents(id) ON DELETE CASCADE\n) STRICT;\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_atoms_doc ON atoms(doc_id);\n\n-- 3. GRAPH_EDGES: The relationships (GraphRAG)\nCREATE TABLE graph_edges (\n    source_atom_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n    target_atom_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n    relation_type TEXT NOT NULL,             -- \u0027SUPPORTS\u0027, \u0027CONTRADICTS\u0027, \u0027CITES\u0027\n    weight REAL DEFAULT 1.0,\n    \n    PRIMARY KEY (source_atom_id, target_atom_id, relation_type),\n    FOREIGN KEY(source_atom_id) REFERENCES atoms(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    FOREIGN KEY(target_atom_id) REFERENCES atoms(id) ON DELETE CASCADE\n) STRICT;\n```\n\n### 2.2 Qdrant Collection Config (Vector)\n**Endpoint:** `http://localhost:6333`\n**Collection Name:** `genio_memory`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"vectors\": {\n    \"size\": 1536,  // Matches \u0027text-embedding-3-small\u0027 or local equivalent\n    \"distance\": \"Cosine\"\n  },\n  \"shard_number\": 1,\n  \"replication_factor\": 1,\n  \"on_disk_payload\": true  // Save RAM, keep metadata on disk\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. RUST CORE: STRUCTS \u0026 TRAITS (THE CONTRACT)\n\n### 3.1 The Knowledge Atom Struct\n**File:** `/core-rust/src/knowledge/models.rs`\n\n```rust\nuse serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};\nuse uuid::Uuid;\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq)]\npub enum TruthStatus {\n    Verified,\n    Disputed,\n    Debunked,\n    Unknown,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct TruthMetadata {\n    pub status: TruthStatus,\n    pub confidence_score: f32, // 0.0 to 1.0\n    pub last_verified_at: i64, // Unix timestamp\n    pub source_links: Vec\u003cString\u003e,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct KnowledgeAtom {\n    pub id: Uuid,\n    pub doc_id: Uuid,\n    pub text: String,\n    pub vector: Option\u003cVec\u003cf32\u003e\u003e,\n    pub truth: TruthMetadata,\n}\n\nimpl KnowledgeAtom {\n    pub fn new(doc_id: Uuid, text: String) -\u003e Self {\n        Self {\n            id: Uuid::new_v4(),\n            doc_id,\n            text,\n            vector: None,\n            truth: TruthMetadata {\n                status: TruthStatus::Unknown,\n                confidence_score: 0.5,\n                last_verified_at: chrono::Utc::now().timestamp(),\n                source_links: vec![],\n            },\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 The Ingestion Trait\n**File:** `/core-rust/src/ingestion/traits.rs`\n\n```rust\nuse async_trait::async_trait;\nuse crate::knowledge::models::KnowledgeAtom;\nuse anyhow::Result;\n\n#[async_trait]\npub trait DocumentParser {\n    /// Accepts a file path, returns a vector of raw text chunks.\n    /// MUST handle PDF, EPUB, and MD.\n    async fn parse(\u0026self, path: \u0026str) -\u003e Result\u003cVec\u003cString\u003e\u003e;\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\npub trait Embedder {\n    /// Converts text to vector.\n    /// MUST support batching to avoid OOM.\n    async fn embed_batch(\u0026self, texts: \u0026[String]) -\u003e Result\u003cVec\u003cVec\u003cf32\u003e\u003e\u003e;\n}\n\npub struct IngestionPipeline\u003cP: DocumentParser, E: Embedder\u003e {\n    pub parser: P,\n    pub embedder: E,\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. ALGORITHMS: THE LOGIC FLOW\n\n### 4.1 Semantic Chunking (The \"Thought Splitter\")\n**File:** `/core-rust/src/ingestion/chunker.rs`\n**Logic:**\nDo NOT use fixed-size chunking. Use **Recursive Character Text Splitter** with Semantic Boundary check.\n\n1.  **Step 1:** Split text by `\\n\\n` (Paragraphs).\n2.  **Step 2:** If paragraph \u003e 1000 chars, split by `. ` (Sentences).\n3.  **Step 3 (Semantic Check):**\n    *   Calculate embedding for Sentence A ($E_a$) and Sentence B ($E_b$).\n    *   Compute Cosine Similarity: $S \u003d \\frac{E_a \\cdot E_b}{||E_a|| ||E_b||}$.\n    *   **Threshold:** If $S \u003c 0.75$, create a hard break (New Atom).\n    *   **Reasoning:** A drop in similarity means the topic changed.\n\n### 4.2 The \"Decay\" Algorithm (Math)\n**File:** `/interface-web/src/utils/decay.ts`\n**Goal:** Calculate visual noise based on data reliability.\n\n```typescript\ninterface DecayParams {\n  lastVerified: number; // Timestamp ms\n  conflictCount: number; // How many sources dispute this?\n  isRetracted: boolean;\n}\n\nexport function calculateDecay(params: DecayParams): React.CSSProperties {\n  const NOW \u003d Date.now();\n  const DAY_MS \u003d 86400000;\n  \n  // 1. Time Decay: Information rots 10% every 30 days if not refreshed\n  const daysOld \u003d (NOW - params.lastVerified) / DAY_MS;\n  const timeDecay \u003d Math.min(daysOld / 300, 0.5); // Max 50% decay from time\n\n  // 2. Conflict Decay: Each conflict adds 20% noise\n  const conflictDecay \u003d Math.min(params.conflictCount * 0.2, 1.0);\n\n  // 3. Total Decay Score (0.0 to 1.0)\n  let totalDecay \u003d timeDecay + conflictDecay;\n  if (params.isRetracted) totalDecay \u003d 1.0;\n\n  // 4. Map to CSS\n  return {\n    opacity: 1 - (totalDecay * 0.5), // Min opacity 0.5\n    filter: `blur(${totalDecay * 2}px) grayscale(${totalDecay * 100}%)`,\n    // Inject random noise via mask if decay \u003e 0.5\n    maskImage: totalDecay \u003e 0.5 ? \u0027url(/noise-texture.png)\u0027 : \u0027none\u0027\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. AGENTIC ROUTER: CONFIGURATION\n\n### 5.1 Router Logic (Rust)\n**File:** `/core-rust/src/agents/router.rs`\n\nThe router decides *where* to send a query based on cost and complexity.\n\n```rust\npub enum ModelTier {\n    Fast,      // Gemini Flash / Haik